itemDescription: Twentieth-century Australian poet and public servant

wikipedia_page.main: Willem Siebenhaar (Dutch pronunciation: [ˈʋɪləm ˈsibənɦaːr]; 28 July 1863 – 29 December 1936) was a social activist and writer in Western Australia from the 1890s until he left Australia in 1924. His literary contributions and opposition to policies such as conscription were his most notable contributions to the history of the state.
